1
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:13,667
Emma, I have good news.

2
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:16,000
Ma'am Olive will leave the house
later at 1:00 o'clock.

3
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:18,200
What if Madam Olive catches you?

4
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,200
She'll send you to jail again.

5
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:21,033
I need to say goodbye.

6
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,367
I need to go.

7
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:24,567
How can I get better
without you?

8
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:26,300
She cries as if she's lost
a child.

9
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:28,600
Mom, that's way out of line!

10
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:30,533
If you're crying
because of Emma,

11
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,633
she has been released
from detention.

12
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,233
I will constantly be
reminded of Mookie

13
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:36,767
if we stay here.

14
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,800
What are you guys
hiding from me?

15
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:41,233
I swear, I'm not keeping
anything from you.

16
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:42,233
Mookie!

17
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:43,567
You can now walk?

18
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:45,667
Are you planning to escape?

19
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:47,500
Do you want to go to Emma?

20
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:49,333
I could've reported you,

21
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:53,033
but I didn't do that
because I respect you.

22
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,133
I said go inside.

23
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,133
Go!

24
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,467
Okay.

25
00:02:01,167 --> 00:02:03,600
I'm sorry if
I lashed out at you.

26
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,533
I didn't mean it.

27
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:11,100
You know how I hate it whenever
you keep secrets from me.

28
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:15,400
I feel like you don't trust me.

29
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:18,533
I'm not just your mom, Mookie.

30
00:02:20,067 --> 00:02:21,367
I'm also your friend.

31
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:34,633
What can I do to...

32
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:38,267
appease you?

33
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:43,400
Will you do it if I tell you?

34
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,033
Mookie, dear.

35
00:02:48,533 --> 00:02:51,500
I don't want us keeping
secrets from each other.

36
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:55,667
If there's something you
want to tell me, then do so.

37
00:02:55,733 --> 00:02:57,400
I'm not going to get mad.

38
00:02:58,633 --> 00:03:01,433
I'm sorry, too,
for everything I did.

39
00:03:04,167 --> 00:03:07,933
But if you really mean
what you said,

40
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:13,333
first of all, I don't want you
to give Flor an earful.

41
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:16,400
I hope you don't get mad at her

42
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:19,033
because she didn't do
anything wrong.

43
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,433
Fine.

44
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,267
I'll do that.

45
00:03:26,233 --> 00:03:27,267
Is there anything else?

46
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:30,667
Second, Mommy...

47
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:36,367
I hope you let Zayn visit me.

48
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,267
He's just being
a good friend to me.

49
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:44,333
I hope we can
welcome him here.

50
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,200
Okay.

51
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:56,967
I will let you have
it on one condition.

52
00:03:57,633 --> 00:04:00,667
He can come when I'm here.

53
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:03,367
And lastly...

54
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:08,233
I hope you'll let me go outside
occasionally.

55
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:15,533
I want to experience what
normal teenagers do.

56
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:21,067
Through that, I can
feel I'm normal.

57
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,400
Mookie, sweetie.

58
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,367
I want the same for you.

59
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:33,567
As long as your health
is not compromised.

60
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:37,167
Because all I want...

61
00:04:39,233 --> 00:04:40,400
is for you to get better.

62
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:58,567
I got rid of Emma,
but Mookie's now the problem.

63
00:04:59,267 --> 00:05:01,633
She demands a lot of things.

64
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,633
All her requests are valid.

65
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,333
She's loyal to Flor.

66
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,333
Mookie's already 17 years old,

67
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,500
so it's normal for her to like
that guy.

68
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:15,333
She just wants to explore
and experience life.

69
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:18,600
To be honest,

70
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,067
I don't know what to do
with Mookie anymore.

71
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,533
Yoy know, I feel like
the feeling is mutual.

72
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:29,667
Mookie doesn't know what
to do with you, too.

73
00:05:31,267 --> 00:05:33,200
She knows exactly what to do.

74
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:38,533
She's threatening me
of reporting me anytime.

75
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,633
She's getting brave.

76
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,367
In this case,

77
00:05:44,433 --> 00:05:47,367
since you know that you're
losing control of her...

78
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:55,433
the best control for this
damage is to control yourself.

79
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:57,467
Control your temper.

80
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:03,267
Mookie won't get close to you
if you're always angry.

81
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:05,167
That's the case.

82
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:11,067
I feel like she's
drifting away from me.

83
00:06:11,167 --> 00:06:15,367
You know, make Mookie feel
that all you want for her

84
00:06:15,433 --> 00:06:17,600
is her best welfare.

85
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:19,233
Be sweet to her.

86
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:22,033
Give her TLC.

87
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:28,433
You're right.

88
00:06:30,767 --> 00:06:37,233
I will give her my
own version of TLC.

89
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:58,233
I have thought
about your request.

90
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:03,933
And since you're
getting better,

91
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:08,567
I thought of bringing you
to my favorite cafe.

92
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:13,400
There are no teenagers there,
but it's a start.

93
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:18,933
And from there, we can go
to the park or museum.

94
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:21,633
Really?

95
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:30,000
Why do you seem like
you're doubtful?

96
00:07:32,467 --> 00:07:34,100
No, Mommy.

97
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,967
There.

98
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:40,333
My baby's already smiling.

99
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:43,100
She's no longer upset.

100
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:47,167
Finish your food.

101
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,433
Here you go, sweetie.

102
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,967
Take your medicines.

103
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:02,567
Are my meds new?

104
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:03,567
Oh, no.

105
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:05,067
It's the same.

106
00:08:05,133 --> 00:08:07,100
You've been taking
that long before.

107
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:08,300
It's just another brand.

108
00:08:11,633 --> 00:08:12,433
Why?

109
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:14,933
Are you doubting me?

110
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,533
No, no.

111
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,967
No, Mommy.

112
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:32,133
That's my good girl.

113
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,467
There.

114
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:47,600
Careful.

115
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:48,700
There.

116
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,267
You're almost there.

117
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:52,433
Just a bit more.

118
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:55,233
There.

119
00:08:58,633 --> 00:08:59,133
Nice.
Okay.

120
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,100
- Thank you, Flor.
- You did well.

121
00:09:07,133 --> 00:09:08,267
You did well.

122
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:15,233
We have a visitor, Mookie.

123
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,600
Look.

124
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:22,900
But they say a black butterfly
brings misfortune.

125
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:26,700
Do you believe such
superstition, Flor?

126
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:29,267
Yes. That's what the elders
in the province say.

127
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:36,733
I don't believe such things.

128
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:39,300
Because for me,

129
00:09:39,367 --> 00:09:43,367
every butterfly is beautiful,
no matter the color.

130
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:48,633
They seem to symbolize hope...

131
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:53,233
like later.

132
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,333
I can go out, Flor.

133
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,033
Yehey.

134
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:58,567
Today is a wonderful day.

135
00:09:58,633 --> 00:09:59,467
Amen.

136
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:14,533
Mookie?

137
00:10:15,633 --> 00:10:16,700
Are you okay?

138
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:17,367
Why?

139
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,267
Mookie!

140
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:21,700
Mookie!

141
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:22,267
Hey!

142
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,167
I will give you away...

143
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,200
instead of just being
kept here in a box.

144
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:22,233
Someone else can make
good use of you.

145
00:11:56,233 --> 00:11:56,767
Mookie! Hey!
Mookie!

146
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:58,400
Ma'am!

147
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,333
Mookie's having a convulsion!

148
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:01,233
Ma'am, what do I do?

149
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,200
Should I call an ambulance?

150
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:03,733
Oh my god!
Mookie!

151
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:05,500
- What do I do?
- Put a throw pillow
on her head.

152
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,200
Okay, Ma'am.

153
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:09,367
Lie her down.

154
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,200
Mookie.

155
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:12,267
- Mookie.
- Don't worry.

156
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,433
She's going to be fine.

157
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,233
Poor Mookie.

158
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:17,533
Mookie, oh no.

159
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:22,100
Go get her oxygen.

160
00:12:22,167 --> 00:12:23,133
Okay.

161
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:25,467
Come on, Mookie.

162
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:28,667
Come on, baby.

163
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:33,500
You're going to be fine.

164
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:36,600
A little more.

165
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:42,567
There.

166
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,133
There.

167
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:47,433
You're fine.

168
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,533
You're okay.

169
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:53,633
You're okay, Mookie.

170
00:13:07,767 --> 00:13:08,700
Don't.

171
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:11,500
Don't.

172
00:13:11,567 --> 00:13:12,433
Ems.
Ems!

173
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:15,133
Ems.

174
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,100
Ems, wake up.

175
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,600
- Ems, you're dreaming.
- Mookie!

176
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:19,600
Mookie!

177
00:13:19,667 --> 00:13:21,467
You were having a nightmare.

178
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,133
Danilo.

179
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:29,600
I was having a bad dream.

180
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:31,167
What did you dream about?

181
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:32,733
It felt real.

182
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:35,133
My nightmare felt real.

183
00:13:36,267 --> 00:13:37,233
It's about Mookie.

184
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:40,433
Her mother was
burying her alive.

185
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,267
She was calling me for help.

186
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:43,767
I was close to her.

187
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:47,500
But when I got to her,
she was already buried.

188
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,367
Danilo, it felt real.

189
00:13:50,433 --> 00:13:51,700
It was so scary.

190
00:13:51,767 --> 00:13:54,600
Danilo.

191
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,567
Same with what happened
to Baby Kayla.

192
00:13:59,667 --> 00:14:00,300
That's enough.

193
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:04,333
You've been seeing Mookie
even in your dreams.

194
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,067
You're having nightmares.

195
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:08,967
Maybe...

196
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:13,133
you should
forget about Mookie.

197
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:17,233
Ems.

198
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:23,300
That's enough.

199
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:24,433
It was just a dream.

200
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:27,033
It was just a dream.

201
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:11,133
Mommy Emma.

202
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:37,300
Why did Mookie have seizures?

203
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,600
What medicine did you give her?

204
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:41,200
Temerogodol.

205
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:42,167
What?

206
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:43,700
Why did you give her that?

207
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:44,633
You shouldn't have
given her that.

208
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,600
And you didn't take
her to the hospital?

209
00:15:46,667 --> 00:15:47,533
Relax.

210
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,233
She's alive, right?

211
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:53,100
And I timed it.

212
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:55,233
Her seizures stopped
before it took five minutes.

213
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:57,300
And if it took more
than five minutes,

214
00:15:57,367 --> 00:15:59,200
I would've brought her
to the hospital.

215
00:15:59,267 --> 00:15:59,633
Okay?

216
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:03,333
Olive, what do you
take Mookie for?

217
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,233
A medical experiment?

218
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,367
Case study?

219
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:18,667
I know what I'm doing
to my child.

220
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:20,367
That's the worst part.

221
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:24,667
I think I'm going to be sick.

222
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:28,500
I feel like throwing up.

223
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:30,300
Drama queen.

224
00:16:30,367 --> 00:16:32,100
My god!

225
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:33,500
Olive!

226
00:16:33,567 --> 00:16:35,467
How could you just stand
there and do nothing?

227
00:16:35,533 --> 00:16:37,967
We should be bringing
Mookie to the hospital!

228
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:39,600
So she can get checked up.

229
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:43,700
I know better
what my child needs.

230
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:47,600
And I'm never bringing
her to the hospital.

231
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:53,767
Olive, I'm indebted to you.

232
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:56,700
But sorry,
I'm going to be blunt.

233
00:16:56,767 --> 00:16:58,700
Stop with your delusions.

234
00:17:00,167 --> 00:17:03,600
You don't know what's
best for Mookie.

235
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,967
Stop playing God to her.

236
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:25,367
You were asleep for hours.

237
00:17:25,433 --> 00:17:29,067
By the way, your Auntie Astrid
came by last night.

238
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:39,500
I didn't know that because
I was sleeping soundly.

239
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:43,067
What happened to me?

240
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:46,000
You had a seizure.

241
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,367
Your condition
is getting worse.

242
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:52,100
But don't worry.

243
00:17:52,567 --> 00:17:54,133
I will take care of you.

244
00:17:54,967 --> 00:17:57,133
Do you want to go
to the garden later?

245
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,700
To get some fresh air?

246
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:00,067
I'll go with you.

247
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:06,133
Mommy, maybe I should
just stay here.

248
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:09,633
I still feel weak and tired.

249
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:13,267
I'll just stay
in the room for now.

250
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,300
Are you sure, sweetie?

251
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:21,200
By the way, my old friend
from medical school

252
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,300
is inviting me out to lunch.

253
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:26,967
But if you don't want me
to go, I will cancel it.

254
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,467
I'll be fine here, Mommy.

255
00:18:30,533 --> 00:18:31,133
Promise.

256
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:38,367
Is your friend a doctor, too?

257
00:18:38,433 --> 00:18:39,967
Yes.

258
00:18:40,033 --> 00:18:43,200
It's been 17 years ago
since I last saw her.

259
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:45,533
The time we graduated
from med school.

260
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:48,067
Class of 2007.

261
00:18:51,167 --> 00:18:53,200
My birth year.

262
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:54,533
Exactly.

263
00:18:56,200 --> 00:19:00,200
I took the board exam
right after graduation.

264
00:19:00,267 --> 00:19:02,100
I was pregnant with you.

265
00:19:02,167 --> 00:19:07,033
I believe you were
my lucky charm.

266
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:09,400
Because that's when
I got my medical license.

267
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:16,667
Notably, Olive Caparas,

268
00:19:16,733 --> 00:19:20,567
who never secured
a medical license.

269
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:23,933
That means my mom
isn't a doctor.

270
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:29,500
After three months,
I gave birth to you.

271
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:33,433
My greatest achievement.

272
00:19:35,767 --> 00:19:38,567
That's why I couldn't
practice being a doctor.

273
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:42,233
Because I wanted to be
a hands-on mom to you.

274
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:48,700
That's why you, my darling,
are my one and only patient.

275
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:55,267
I find you strange, dear.

276
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,000
I'm not used to this.

277
00:19:58,067 --> 00:19:59,633
Are you really thinking
about business?

278
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:03,167
You should get
used to this, Mom.

279
00:20:03,267 --> 00:20:08,333
It's better to do business while
I'm still looking for a job.

280
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:12,100
As Dan said, it's not that much,
but it's still a big help.

281
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:14,467
You know, your husband is right.

282
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:16,500
Money matters in this world.

283
00:20:16,567 --> 00:20:18,733
You're worthless without money.

284
00:20:24,067 --> 00:20:24,700
I agree, Mom.

285
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:31,167
All I want is to help
with our expenses.

286
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:33,033
And who knows?

287
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,433
We might make it big by
selling turon and banana cue.

288
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:37,600
I might not have
to go back to work.

289
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:41,233
That's a good idea.

290
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:45,233
You'll be busy.

291
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,700
You won't think of Mookie.

292
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,433
Son of a gun.

293
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,333
I forgot about this.

294
00:20:58,267 --> 00:20:59,767
The mayor will give out
financial assistance

295
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,133
at the basketball court.

296
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:04,200
Wiro wants me to go.

297
00:21:04,267 --> 00:21:05,367
Go ahead.

298
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:06,467
You don't want to
miss that chance.

299
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:08,200
That's money.

300
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,233
How about you?

301
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:11,300
How about these?

302
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:12,233
I got this.

303
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:13,267
I can manage.

304
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:14,400
I'll bring that home.

305
00:21:14,467 --> 00:21:15,400
Are you sure?
Yes, I can manage.

306
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:17,000
Give it to me.

307
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,033
Thank you, dear.

308
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:18,667
Yes, Mom.
I don't want to waste it.

309
00:21:19,233 --> 00:21:20,033
Yes, that's money.
- We don't want to waste it.
- Okay.

310
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,333
- I'll get going. Thank you.
- Bye, Mom.

311
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:30,267
You should be careful!

312
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,500
You again?

313
00:22:46,167 --> 00:22:47,433
How may I help you, Mookie?

314
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:50,233
Weren't you
my pediatrician before?

315
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:55,300
I want to know about my
illnesses since I was a child.

316
00:22:55,367 --> 00:22:56,800
You were in perfect health.

317
00:22:56,867 --> 00:22:59,500
You weren't sick when you
were a child, Mookie.

318
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:02,200
I took care of and raised
Mookie for 17 years.

319
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:03,700
And here you are,

320
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:07,500
coming into our lives to ruin
my relationship with my child!

321
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:09,133
I treat Mookie as my own.

322
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:12,000
She isn't your dead child!

323
00:23:12,067 --> 00:23:13,333
Darn you!

324
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,133
Ouch!

325
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,600
You did the right thing.

326
00:23:15,667 --> 00:23:17,167
She should get
what she deserves,

327
00:23:17,233 --> 00:23:18,067
even just for once.

328
00:23:18,133 --> 00:23:21,167
I'm worried that she'll
come back for you.

329
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:24,467
Can you search what
medicine this is?

330
00:23:24,567 --> 00:23:26,333
Do you think I'm a monster?

331
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:28,000
That I'm a horrible mother?

332
00:23:28,067 --> 00:23:30,000
I talked to Mookie yesterday.

333
00:23:30,067 --> 00:23:33,067
And she was asking about
her medical history.

334
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:35,500
My medical records are
kept in my mom's room.

335
00:23:35,567 --> 00:23:37,000
I need to see them.

336
00:23:37,067 --> 00:23:38,967
I need to know
the truth, Zayn.
